WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:01.867
<i> Previously on "diggstown".</i>

00:02.002 --> 00:03.068
Seriously, doug?

00:03.203 --> 00:04.436
I just don't want you to
get chewed up by some creep

00:04.571 --> 00:05.570
Twice your age.

00:05.639 --> 00:06.438
Leah:
<i> I've seen the</i>
<i> woman you date.</i>

00:06.573 --> 00:07.606
Age ain't nothing
but a number, eh?

00:07.675 --> 00:09.307
We didn't raise
you to be stupid.

00:09.343 --> 00:11.844
Marcie:
<i> Rolanda, you don't</i>
<i> want to go with him.</i>

00:11.846 --> 00:13.011
<i> Why do you need</i>
<i> a lawyer today?</i>

00:13.080 --> 00:14.345
Trudy:
<i> Basil's from jamaica.</i>

00:14.382 --> 00:16.348
He's a migrant worker
at goldenview fields.

00:16.350 --> 00:18.050
These people are no good,
ms. Diggs.

00:18.185 --> 00:20.786
Mel:
<i> Whatever this thing is</i>
<i> that you're holding onto,</i>

00:20.788 --> 00:22.554
<i> You're gonna have to</i>
<i> get real about it</i>

00:22.556 --> 00:25.190
Or it will continue
to eat at you.

00:25.192 --> 00:27.826
[ominous music]

00:28.796 --> 00:31.463
Ned:
<i> Psst, come on.</i>

00:31.532 --> 00:33.065
<i> Get up.</i>

00:36.804 --> 00:41.773
[ominous music]
[man groaning]

00:43.577 --> 00:44.476
Basil:
<i> What's going on?</i>

00:44.611 --> 00:45.510
[car engine revving]

00:45.579 --> 00:47.112
Ned:
<i> Come on, let's go.</i>

00:50.117 --> 00:51.883
Where are we heading?

00:51.919 --> 00:57.756
[ominous music]

00:57.891 --> 01:01.026
♪

01:01.161 --> 01:04.963
[boat engine revving]

01:05.099 --> 01:11.203
[ominous music swells]

01:12.839 --> 01:15.006
Mel:
<i> Have you experienced more</i>
<i>dreams about your aunt rolanda?</i>

01:19.446 --> 01:21.379
Nothing in the last
couple of weeks.

01:23.284 --> 01:26.251
Since I told my mom about...

01:27.254 --> 01:28.754
Mel:
<i> Say it out loud.</i>

01:29.556 --> 01:31.056
It'll help.

01:34.261 --> 01:36.595
Marcie:
<i> About rolanda's</i>
<i> suicide attempt.</i>

01:38.799 --> 01:40.332
Mel:
How does that feel?

01:40.868 --> 01:41.767
Difficult.

01:41.902 --> 01:43.335
Mel:
<i> Why do you think</i>
<i> you have trouble</i>

01:43.470 --> 01:46.070
Verbalizing your
feelings about this?

01:46.107 --> 01:47.606
Marcie:
<i> I feel responsible.</i>

01:50.010 --> 01:51.543
You know, after what
happened at the beach,

01:51.678 --> 01:53.011
I-I-I could have
said something,

01:53.047 --> 01:55.079
I could have done...

01:55.116 --> 01:56.615
I could have done
things differently.

01:56.617 --> 02:00.585
Mel:
<i> But you aren't responsible</i>
<i>for your aunt's actions, marcie.</i>

02:01.488 --> 02:04.155
We can't control
what others do.

02:04.157 --> 02:08.226
<i> When someone engages</i>
<i> in suicidal ideations,</i>

02:08.262 --> 02:10.228
The signs are
often confusing.

02:11.532 --> 02:15.033
<i> One doesn't always know</i>
<i> what resources are available,</i>

02:15.035 --> 02:17.835
Or what actions to take.

02:17.872 --> 02:19.470
Marcie:
<i> Yeah well...</i>

02:21.708 --> 02:22.708
I should've done something.

02:22.710 --> 02:24.910
You did do something.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.180
In that moment,

02:28.182 --> 02:29.781
You saved her.

02:32.019 --> 02:33.518
Stop blaming yourself.

02:33.521 --> 02:35.119
[marcie sighs]

02:37.525 --> 02:39.457
I just keep thinking
about my dad.

02:39.459 --> 02:40.726
Like, what am I...

02:40.728 --> 02:42.126
God, what am I
gonna say to him?

02:42.163 --> 02:43.128
What is he gonna
say to me?

02:43.263 --> 02:44.763
Stop speculating.

02:45.866 --> 02:47.332
Sit down with your dad.

02:48.502 --> 02:50.268
Tell him the truth.

02:50.337 --> 02:53.004
[gentle music]

02:53.073 --> 02:54.673
[thunder rolls]

02:54.742 --> 02:56.808
[rain pattering]

02:56.844 --> 03:01.013
[indistinct chatter]

03:01.148 --> 03:02.281
Marcie:
<i> Hey emily!</i>

03:02.283 --> 03:03.281
<i> Sorry I'm late.</i>

03:03.417 --> 03:05.516
No worries, you're
doing me a huge favour.

03:05.553 --> 03:07.819
Enough stuff at howard's
to fill two houses.

03:07.955 --> 03:08.820
Hey, howard.

03:08.956 --> 03:09.887
Howard:
<i> How you doing, marcie?</i>

03:09.924 --> 03:12.156
Be gentle with
my baby, okay?

03:12.193 --> 03:13.825
Your baby?

03:13.961 --> 03:18.163
So you guys are really
doing this, huh?

03:18.232 --> 03:19.364
I never thought
I'd see the day

03:19.433 --> 03:21.499
When you and your ex
would share a roof again.

03:21.501 --> 03:22.768
Me neither.

03:22.770 --> 03:23.901
But he needs a place here

03:23.938 --> 03:25.437
When he's not
travelling with his acts

03:25.572 --> 03:27.973
And it's better for
both of us financially.

03:28.108 --> 03:30.909
And the kids know that
mom and dad aren't-

03:31.044 --> 03:32.744
Yes, yes, yes!

03:32.780 --> 03:34.446
They know mom still
likes girls, okay?

03:34.581 --> 03:35.513
Okay. All right.

03:35.549 --> 03:36.514
Look I gotta run,

03:36.550 --> 03:37.782
But you coming to
the show tomorrow?

03:37.851 --> 03:39.784
Some of howard's
artists are performing.

03:39.820 --> 03:41.519
I wouldn't miss it.

03:41.555 --> 03:42.954
Emily:
<i> Hey.</i>

03:44.391 --> 03:46.658
Howard:<i> I'm coming.</i>
<i> -</i> Ms. Diggs!

03:46.727 --> 03:49.094
<i> Hey, uh, trudy, right?</i>

03:49.163 --> 03:51.529
<i> Your boyfriend is basil.</i>

03:51.565 --> 03:52.598
Immigration issue.

03:52.733 --> 03:55.267
You...You guys were supposed
to see me yesterday.

03:55.269 --> 03:56.267
Basil's gone.

03:56.303 --> 03:58.270
We were supposed to
meet yesterday but he...

03:58.339 --> 03:59.338
He never showed.

03:59.340 --> 04:01.406
I-I can't reach him.

04:01.408 --> 04:03.007
He's just gone.

04:03.611 --> 04:06.945
[mysterious music]

04:07.080 --> 04:10.082
Trudy:
<i> Basil is desperate to leave</i>
<i> his job at goldenview fields,</i>

04:10.217 --> 04:12.617
But if he does he'll
get sent back to jamaica

04:12.620 --> 04:14.086
So we've been looking
at different ways

04:14.088 --> 04:16.288
To get him
canadian residency.

04:16.290 --> 04:17.756
Marcie:
<i> Goldenview?</i>

04:17.758 --> 04:18.890
Heard that name.

04:19.025 --> 04:20.392
Isn't that the
frozen veggie brand?

04:20.527 --> 04:22.760
Trudy:
<i> It's a megafarm owned</i>
<i> by the clawford family.</i>

04:22.796 --> 04:24.362
Didn't one of their
sons run for mayor

04:24.498 --> 04:25.363
A few years back?

04:25.399 --> 04:26.365
Brian.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.500
When was the last time
that you spoke to basil?

04:28.635 --> 04:29.868
Two days ago.

04:30.003 --> 04:31.903
He was supposed to meet
me yesterday morning,

04:32.039 --> 04:33.972
But he never showed.

04:34.107 --> 04:37.476
<i> No calls, no texts,</i>
<i> just nothing.</i>

04:37.611 --> 04:39.511
Has he ever done anything
like this before,

04:39.580 --> 04:41.045
Just stop responding?

04:41.081 --> 04:42.781
No, never.

04:42.850 --> 04:44.249
Alarm bells were
going off for me

04:44.318 --> 04:46.051
So I tried calling
goldenview where he works,

04:46.053 --> 04:46.985
But ned wouldn't even-

04:47.054 --> 04:49.254
Who is ned?
-The foreman.

04:49.389 --> 04:50.589
He completely
brushed me off.

04:50.724 --> 04:51.590
Marcie:
<i> Alarm bells?</i>

04:51.725 --> 04:53.258
Why was that?

04:57.798 --> 04:59.197
Um...

05:00.167 --> 05:01.199
Hey, if you want
us to help you,

05:01.268 --> 05:02.867
You have to tell
us everything.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.742
Basil's 18-year-old
brother desmond

05:10.811 --> 05:11.943
Came to work
for goldenview

05:12.012 --> 05:14.412
For the first
time this year.

05:14.481 --> 05:16.414
Basil had done it
four years running

05:16.450 --> 05:18.783
And convinced him it was gonna
be a great way to make money.

05:18.852 --> 05:21.753
But about a
month ago,

05:23.724 --> 05:25.323
Desmond died
on the job.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.458
What happened?

05:27.494 --> 05:29.360
Ned had desmond
driving a tractor,

05:29.396 --> 05:31.963
Which he wasn't
properly trained to do,

05:32.099 --> 05:33.098
Through the fields

05:33.167 --> 05:36.168
And the tractor
overturned into a ditch.

05:36.170 --> 05:38.336
<i> Basil didn't even get</i>
<i> to say goodbye to him.</i>

05:38.339 --> 05:40.304
I'm sorry, that
sounds like a,

05:40.341 --> 05:41.640
Sounds like a
terrible accident.

05:41.775 --> 05:44.242
Trudy:
<i> It wasn't an accident.</i>

05:44.244 --> 05:47.445
<i> That child had no business</i>
<i>driving that piece of equipment.</i>

05:47.481 --> 05:49.748
The kid didn't even
have a driver's licence.

05:49.817 --> 05:52.350
<i> You know they waited an</i>
<i> hour to call an ambulance?</i>

05:53.520 --> 05:55.020
Ellery:
<i> You're saying they</i>
<i> let the kid die?</i>

05:55.889 --> 05:56.955
Marcie:
<i> And I'm guessing</i>

05:56.957 --> 05:59.891
<i> Basil was asking way</i>
<i> too many questions.</i>

06:00.026 --> 06:00.959
Trudy:
<i> Basil was furious.</i>

06:01.028 --> 06:02.027
His little
brother's death

06:02.029 --> 06:04.396
Was completely
preventable.

06:04.465 --> 06:06.330
He threatened to
report goldenview

06:06.367 --> 06:07.999
To the migrant
workers' alliance.

06:10.070 --> 06:12.204
Things are bad enough
for migrant workers.

06:13.240 --> 06:14.839
Work shouldn't be
a death sentence.

06:16.410 --> 06:18.210
Well, it sounds
like he may have

06:18.345 --> 06:19.477
A wrongful
death claim.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.079
Did he go to the police?

06:21.081 --> 06:23.047
A migrant worker
going to the police?

06:24.084 --> 06:25.550
Please.

06:26.120 --> 06:27.552
Let's find basil.

06:28.455 --> 06:29.387
<i> We'll start at</i>
<i> the last place</i>

06:29.423 --> 06:31.088
<i> We know he</i>
<i> was for sure.</i>

06:31.125 --> 06:32.657
Goldenview fields.

06:33.326 --> 06:34.892
Thank you.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.563
Well, here we
have my desk.

06:39.466 --> 06:41.399
Oh, receptionist.

06:41.468 --> 06:43.901
Ooh.
-And last but not least...

06:43.937 --> 06:44.969
Mini fridge.

06:44.971 --> 06:46.237
A mini fridge?
-Yes.

06:46.273 --> 06:48.840
Avery, now that
is impressive.

06:48.975 --> 06:50.475
What can I say?

06:51.077 --> 06:52.711
Have a seat.

06:52.713 --> 06:54.512
So I spoke to ona.

06:54.648 --> 06:55.513
Okay.

06:55.549 --> 06:57.115
She said the hold
up with processing

06:57.184 --> 06:59.517
The contact requests
is normal.

06:59.586 --> 07:01.586
It's to give the birth
parents time to file a veto

07:01.588 --> 07:03.554
If they don't wish
to be contacted.

07:05.793 --> 07:07.992
I keep thinking this
wasn't the right call.

07:08.929 --> 07:09.428
<i> I mean, I had</i>
<i> great parents,</i>

07:09.563 --> 07:10.595
A great childhood.

07:10.597 --> 07:11.863
Seeking out
birth parents

07:11.998 --> 07:14.800
Can bring up a lot of
complicated emotions.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.667
It's just,

07:16.703 --> 07:20.105
It's made me feel so
isolated, you know?

07:20.240 --> 07:22.107
Have you spoken to
marcie about it?

07:22.109 --> 07:23.775
Yeah, marcie's...

07:23.910 --> 07:26.545
She's got her own stuff

07:26.547 --> 07:28.112
Since the shooting.

07:30.217 --> 07:31.682
Yeah.

07:34.154 --> 07:35.287
Iris, I'm-I'm sorry.

07:35.289 --> 07:36.354
I wasn't even thinking, I-

07:36.356 --> 07:37.955
That's okay.

07:38.892 --> 07:40.558
Things with cliff
and I were new,

07:41.662 --> 07:45.296
But I keep dwelling on
what could have been,

07:45.365 --> 07:47.164
Which kind of makes
things worse.

07:47.734 --> 07:49.567
Yeah, I get it.

07:50.671 --> 07:51.903
He was a good man.

07:52.038 --> 07:53.604
Yeah, he was.

07:55.509 --> 07:59.043
Look, if you ever need an ear,
I'm here.

08:00.113 --> 08:01.679
I mean that.

08:03.350 --> 08:04.716
Thanks.

08:06.520 --> 08:09.320
So tell me more about
this mini fridge, please.

08:11.625 --> 08:14.626
Howard:
<i> Halifax music scene</i>
<i> is on fire right now.</i>

08:14.695 --> 08:15.994
I just signed
three new artists

08:15.996 --> 08:17.596
In the last six months alone.

08:17.598 --> 08:18.863
What kind of acts?

08:18.866 --> 08:22.133
These two killer vocalists
and one amazing jazz pianist.

08:22.202 --> 08:24.002
They'll all be at
the show tomorrow.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.070
Velma:
<i> Ooh, great.</i>

08:25.205 --> 08:26.738
Dad, can I get these?

08:28.876 --> 08:31.475
You know you
spoil these kids.

08:31.512 --> 08:33.545
Am I spoiling them or am
I loving them too much?

08:33.680 --> 08:35.580
And is, is there
such a thing, velma?

08:36.683 --> 08:38.182
Always good with words.

08:41.154 --> 08:42.620
<i> Got enough money yet?</i>

08:42.756 --> 08:43.955
Michael:
<i> Yep.</i>

08:44.024 --> 08:46.558
I'm so glad you and emily
are giving this another go.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.093
Sharing the same roof?

08:48.095 --> 08:49.694
Yeah, well, me too.

08:49.696 --> 08:51.963
Nice having everybody
together again and so far,

08:52.098 --> 08:53.631
It's working out
pretty well.

08:55.802 --> 08:56.701
Good man.

08:56.836 --> 08:57.702
Michael:
<i> Thanks a lot.</i>

08:57.837 --> 08:58.770
Velma:
<i> Thank you.</i>

08:58.905 --> 09:00.438
You're welcome.

09:01.241 --> 09:07.112
[mysterious music]

09:07.247 --> 09:11.582
♪

09:11.618 --> 09:13.051
[phone chiming]

09:13.053 --> 09:20.592
[mysterious music]

09:20.661 --> 09:22.594
Can I help you ladies?

09:22.663 --> 09:23.961
That's ned.

09:23.997 --> 09:25.129
Stay here.

09:25.165 --> 09:28.066
Hi, I'm marcie diggs.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.934
I represent basil allen,
one of your workers.

09:30.003 --> 09:30.935
Is he here?

09:31.004 --> 09:33.405
Ned flores,
grounds manager.

09:33.540 --> 09:34.672
Sorry you made it
all this way but

09:34.708 --> 09:36.608
Basil allen ran off.

09:36.677 --> 09:38.143
What do you mean ran off?

09:38.278 --> 09:40.211
It happens a lot with
migrant workers.

09:40.213 --> 09:41.479
We bring 'em here
on contract,

09:41.515 --> 09:44.249
<i> Then first chance they get,</i>
<i> poof, in the wind.</i>

09:44.384 --> 09:45.650
You're lying!
-Trudy!

09:45.786 --> 09:46.685
What happened to him?!

09:46.820 --> 09:47.885
I know you did
something to him!

09:47.921 --> 09:49.020
Trudy! Trudy!

09:49.155 --> 09:50.721
Have a good day, ladies.

09:51.391 --> 09:53.158
Come on, come on.

09:53.160 --> 09:55.093
[mysterious music]

09:56.563 --> 09:58.696
Michelle:
<i> You break it,</i>
<i> you buy it [giggles].</i>

09:58.732 --> 10:00.632
Doug:
<i> The space looks incredible.</i>

10:00.767 --> 10:02.467
Michelle:
<i> It exceeds my wildest dreams.</i>

10:02.602 --> 10:04.502
Doug:
<i> Don't you get any ideas</i>
<i> about the wedding now.</i>

10:04.504 --> 10:05.337
The second time around

10:05.472 --> 10:06.738
Is supposed to be
more intimate, dummy.

10:06.873 --> 10:08.106
[doug chuckles]

10:08.175 --> 10:09.741
Michelle:
<i> I'm still so grateful</i>
<i> to viv for her donation.</i>

10:09.876 --> 10:12.676
Well, she puts her money
where her mouth is.

10:12.678 --> 10:13.577
<i> About that,</i>

10:13.614 --> 10:15.079
I heard about eskasoni.

10:15.148 --> 10:17.114
<i> Viv wants to move</i>
<i> forward immediately.</i>

10:17.150 --> 10:19.050
That's great news!

10:19.185 --> 10:20.218
Yeah.

10:20.220 --> 10:21.786
I'm sensing a but here.

10:21.921 --> 10:23.487
I'd have to do it on my own.

10:24.491 --> 10:25.589
Leave marcie's firm.

10:25.626 --> 10:26.957
Yeah.

10:26.994 --> 10:29.327
This has been a dream of yours
for as long as I've known you.

10:29.329 --> 10:30.862
Doug:
<i> Well viv sees</i>
<i> something in me</i>

10:30.864 --> 10:32.197
If she's giving me an
opportunity like this.

10:32.199 --> 10:33.932
Marcie would want
you to do this.

10:35.002 --> 10:36.100
<i> Seriously.</i>

10:36.169 --> 10:40.004
<i> Douglas, these are</i>
<i> all good things.</i>

10:40.007 --> 10:40.938
For us,

10:41.008 --> 10:42.774
For the community,

10:42.909 --> 10:43.941
For you.

10:44.011 --> 10:51.816
[soft dramatic music]

10:53.020 --> 10:54.619
Marcie:
<i> Okay, if we're gonna</i>
<i> work together,</i>

10:54.621 --> 10:55.754
You have to listen to me.

10:55.889 --> 10:58.156
Ned's the one who does
their dirty work.

10:58.158 --> 10:59.758
<i> He was the one who</i>
<i> wouldn't call the doctor</i>

10:59.893 --> 11:01.559
The night basil's
little brother died.

11:01.561 --> 11:03.695
Trudy, I know how you feel,
I really do.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.130
He was lying!

11:05.265 --> 11:07.232
Okay, basil wouldn't
just run off.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.100
Basil told cruz he was
gonna make a complaint to-

11:09.235 --> 11:10.768
Wait, who's cruz?

11:10.804 --> 11:12.237
He's another migrant worker,

11:12.372 --> 11:14.239
<i> Someone basil</i>
<i> considered a friend.</i>

11:14.241 --> 11:16.841
But cruz betrayed him
and went straight to ned.

11:16.843 --> 11:18.243
Basil confronted
him about it

11:18.378 --> 11:20.378
And the two just got
into a huge fight

11:20.380 --> 11:21.779
And it just got really ugly.

11:21.915 --> 11:23.381
Okay, can we talk to him?

11:23.516 --> 11:24.549
I think he got sent to pei.

11:24.684 --> 11:25.917
Pei?

11:25.986 --> 11:28.085
Trudy:
<i> They've got farms across</i>
<i> all four provinces.</i>

11:28.121 --> 11:30.988
<i> Now cruz manages the private</i>
<i> home where the parents live.</i>

11:32.693 --> 11:34.258
Iris, you got a second?

11:35.095 --> 11:36.227
What's up?

11:36.296 --> 11:37.862
Marcie:
<i> I need some background</i>
<i> on a company,</i>

11:37.864 --> 11:39.263
Goldenview fields.

11:39.299 --> 11:40.398
The salad bag company?

11:40.533 --> 11:41.766
Marcie:
<i> I want to know</i>
<i> about that company.</i>

11:41.901 --> 11:43.067
I want to know
about the family.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.069
Any complaints,
scandals, you name it.

11:45.072 --> 11:46.404
On it.

11:46.539 --> 11:49.207
Marcie:
<i> Ellery, can you go to</i>
<i> pei to the family estate?</i>

11:49.276 --> 11:50.808
See if you can get
cruz to speak to you.

11:50.877 --> 11:51.876
Great.

11:52.011 --> 11:54.245
Let's hope I don't end
up in jail... Again.

11:54.281 --> 11:55.747
Fingers crossed.

11:55.749 --> 11:59.584
[soft dramatic music]

12:00.253 --> 12:01.819
[knocking on door]

12:01.855 --> 12:03.220
Bad time?

12:03.256 --> 12:04.855
Define "good time."

12:05.425 --> 12:06.891
Basil allen?

12:07.461 --> 12:08.493
<i> Iris told me.</i>

12:08.628 --> 12:12.163
Wading through the web
that is goldenview fields.

12:12.298 --> 12:13.831
Ah, the clawfords.

12:13.867 --> 12:14.899
Self-made,

12:14.901 --> 12:16.167
<i> Just shy of the</i>
<i> billionaires club.</i>

12:16.302 --> 12:17.201
You're going up
against them?

12:17.270 --> 12:18.903
Marcie:
<i> It's too soon to tell, but...</i>

12:21.274 --> 12:23.674
I don't know, something
just doesn't feel right.

12:25.078 --> 12:27.812
Doug:
<i> So, um, vivian</i>
<i> wants to get moving</i>

12:27.947 --> 12:29.680
On the eskasoni legal clinic.

12:31.317 --> 12:32.850
Separate from the firm.

12:35.388 --> 12:37.121
So you're leaving?

12:37.124 --> 12:38.456
I'm considering it.

12:38.525 --> 12:40.058
It's a huge opportunity.

12:42.362 --> 12:43.928
It is. Yeah.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.064
<i> Boy, she's smart.</i>

12:46.199 --> 12:48.499
Dismantling the firm
from the inside.

12:48.535 --> 12:49.600
This isn't about that.

12:49.736 --> 12:51.235
Isn't it?

12:52.773 --> 12:53.871
Of course.

12:53.940 --> 12:56.540
I'm sorry, yeah,
it's-it's about you.

12:56.576 --> 12:59.677
Marcie:
<i> You have to admit the timing</i>
<i> is a little convenient,</i>

12:59.713 --> 13:00.812
Don't you think?

13:00.814 --> 13:02.680
I can't believe we're
having this conversation.

13:02.816 --> 13:04.649
<i> You really can't fathom</i>
<i> that this is about vivian</i>

13:04.784 --> 13:06.550
Acknowledging
that I can lead?

13:07.220 --> 13:11.823
[tense dramatic music]

13:11.958 --> 13:13.758
I guess that's it then.

13:13.893 --> 13:19.764
[tense music swells]

13:22.502 --> 13:28.439
Ysterious music]

13:28.508 --> 13:31.108
♪

13:31.144 --> 13:32.710
You in court today?

13:35.348 --> 13:36.381
You okay?

13:36.383 --> 13:38.583
Oh yeah, sorry,
in my head.

13:40.387 --> 13:41.919
[sighs] birth parent stuff.

13:41.988 --> 13:44.355
Well I've got time if you
want to talk about it.

13:46.993 --> 13:48.559
I just keep thinking,

13:50.997 --> 13:52.463
Was it right to reach out?

13:53.600 --> 13:54.899
Of course it was.

13:55.035 --> 13:56.534
My life was settled,
marcie, it was good.

13:56.603 --> 13:59.938
It's just now everything
feels unsettled and weird.

13:59.940 --> 14:02.573
Marcie, I know you asked
not to be interrupted

14:02.609 --> 14:03.641
But there's a courier here

14:03.710 --> 14:04.943
<i> With a letter you</i>
<i> have to sign off on.</i>

14:04.945 --> 14:06.344
Okay, um...

14:07.013 --> 14:08.146
One minute, okay?

14:08.148 --> 14:09.714
Yeah, yeah.

14:13.153 --> 14:16.287
[avery sighs deeply]

14:17.223 --> 14:18.623
[marcie scoffs]

14:21.194 --> 14:24.095
A letter of complaint from
the barrister's society.

14:24.097 --> 14:27.164
Judge dewey is accusing me
of professional misconduct.

14:27.200 --> 14:28.099
Can you believe this?

14:28.234 --> 14:30.668
What?!
-Damn it.

14:30.670 --> 14:32.603
I mean, as if I
need this right now

14:32.672 --> 14:34.172
On top of everything else-

14:38.411 --> 14:39.410
It can wait.

14:39.446 --> 14:40.979
No, marcie just take
care of your business.

14:41.114 --> 14:42.413
Nope, you were telling me...

14:42.548 --> 14:45.350
Marcie, handle your business.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.185
I'll see you at home.

14:47.187 --> 14:53.057
[soft dramatic music]

14:53.059 --> 14:56.994
♪

15:03.003 --> 15:04.736
Yeah, I believe it's her.

15:04.871 --> 15:06.504
Are you cruz diaz?

15:06.506 --> 15:07.471
My name is ellery lopez-

15:07.507 --> 15:09.139
I already know
who you are.

15:09.175 --> 15:10.341
They would like
to speak to you.

15:10.476 --> 15:15.680
[dark mysterious music]

15:15.749 --> 15:16.880
Hello?

15:16.917 --> 15:18.549
Lester:
<i> Ms. Lopez,</i>
<i> welcome to the island.</i>

15:19.619 --> 15:20.551
Who is this?

15:20.587 --> 15:21.919
Lester:
<i> Lester larocque.</i>

15:21.922 --> 15:23.220
<i> We understand you</i>
<i> have some questions</i>

15:23.290 --> 15:26.490
<i> Regarding mr. Diaz and his</i>
<i> relationship to basil allen.</i>

15:26.492 --> 15:27.925
<i> Mr. Diaz would like</i>
<i> any communication</i>

15:28.060 --> 15:29.527
<i> Run through our office.</i>

15:30.330 --> 15:31.495
<i> We're on prince street.</i>

15:31.497 --> 15:33.464
<i> Why don't you come in</i>
<i> and we'll have a chat?</i>

15:36.836 --> 15:38.869
<i> Ms. Lopez, glad</i>
<i> you could join us.</i>

15:38.905 --> 15:40.171
Let's forego the niceties,

15:40.240 --> 15:42.106
You obviously know
why I'm here.

15:42.175 --> 15:44.709
<i> I'm looking for a migrant</i>
<i> worker, basil allen.</i>

15:44.844 --> 15:46.344
Andrea? What are you-

15:46.346 --> 15:47.578
Andrea:
<i> I'm not happy</i>
<i> about this either.</i>

15:47.714 --> 15:49.913
I'm in the middle of five
real estate closings.

15:49.950 --> 15:51.182
Take it up with brian.

15:51.251 --> 15:52.183
Nice hair.

15:52.252 --> 15:53.818
Fine, just have a seat.

16:00.327 --> 16:02.526
Andrea:
<i> Please. Continue.</i>

16:02.595 --> 16:03.794
Where were we?

16:03.930 --> 16:06.064
Your missing employee,
basil allen.

16:06.066 --> 16:07.065
Right. Well ms. Lopez,

16:07.067 --> 16:08.866
We have some
information for you.

16:09.669 --> 16:10.835
What are these?

16:10.904 --> 16:12.737
Lester:
<i> Basil allen's emails,</i>
<i> text messages.</i>

16:12.872 --> 16:14.472
Invasions of his privacy?

16:14.474 --> 16:16.340
Andrea:
<i> Employees have no</i>
<i> expectation of privacy</i>

16:16.343 --> 16:18.676
If the correspondence was
happening on company devices.

16:18.745 --> 16:20.945
His personal cellphone
isn't a company device.

16:20.947 --> 16:22.346
Lester:
<i> It recently came</i>
<i> to our attention</i>

16:22.349 --> 16:23.681
<i> That mr. Allen has</i>
<i> been attempting</i>

16:23.683 --> 16:25.950
<i> To change his</i>
<i> immigration status.</i>

16:26.085 --> 16:27.952
<i> He had been conducting</i>
<i> online relationships</i>

16:28.087 --> 16:30.488
With multiple women in
the hopes of marrying one

16:30.557 --> 16:32.623
To fast track his
canadian residency.

16:32.759 --> 16:34.625
It's our belief that
he finally succeeded

16:34.694 --> 16:36.427
And ran off with
one of these women.

16:38.631 --> 16:39.496
Process server:
<i> You sure about this?</i>

16:39.532 --> 16:40.431
Vivian:
<i> Yes, absolutely certain.</i>

16:40.566 --> 16:41.665
Process server:
<i> Okay.</i>

16:41.735 --> 16:43.834
Make sure it's done by
the end of the week.

16:43.836 --> 16:45.102
I don't want to be
where I'm not wanted.

16:45.138 --> 16:46.103
Process server:
<i> Okay.</i>

16:46.239 --> 16:47.504
[phone beeping]
hold on.

16:47.540 --> 16:49.139
Oh, I have to take this.

16:50.043 --> 16:52.910
Doug! I was just
about to call you.

16:52.912 --> 16:55.379
Dinner tonight, my place?

16:55.448 --> 16:58.583
I have a special
surprise for you.

16:58.718 --> 17:00.284
Thank you.

17:01.320 --> 17:04.655
Clawford's lawyer
produced evidence

17:04.657 --> 17:08.059
That basil was pursuing
romantic relationships

17:08.128 --> 17:10.327
<i> To secure himself</i>
<i> canadian citizenship.</i>

17:12.632 --> 17:14.465
I'm sorry but,

17:14.534 --> 17:17.668
I don't think you were the
only woman in his life.

17:17.670 --> 17:20.938
I was his only
real relationship.

17:22.008 --> 17:24.275
He didn't love any
of the others.

17:24.344 --> 17:25.877
Wait, you knew about this?

17:27.147 --> 17:30.013
It was the fastest way for
him to get citizenship.

17:30.050 --> 17:32.150
Why didn't you
marry him then?

17:34.620 --> 17:36.087
I'm already married.

17:36.222 --> 17:37.288
[marcie sighs]

17:37.357 --> 17:40.124
My ex and I we just,
we couldn't afford a divorce.

17:40.259 --> 17:41.625
[phone chiming]

17:45.698 --> 17:47.398
It's a text from basil.

17:47.400 --> 17:48.732
<i> "I'm being taken on a truck,</i>

17:48.768 --> 17:49.967
"I don't know where.

17:50.036 --> 17:52.236
"may not make it to the
meeting tomorrow."

17:52.371 --> 17:53.904
Marcie:
<i> Wait, tomorrow?</i>

17:56.242 --> 17:58.042
We were supposed to
meet two days ago.

17:58.177 --> 18:03.113
[ominous music]

18:05.785 --> 18:07.919
I'm feeling this
look for you.

18:08.054 --> 18:09.921
I haven't even taken
off the tags yet.

18:11.791 --> 18:12.890
I honestly don't think

18:12.892 --> 18:14.658
I can take another one
of your surprises, viv.

18:14.727 --> 18:17.661
Relax. I want you to
think of our project

18:17.730 --> 18:21.132
As a real homecoming.

18:21.267 --> 18:28.139
[soft dramatic music]

18:28.274 --> 18:29.773
Hey dad.

18:31.077 --> 18:32.509
Leah.

18:36.549 --> 18:42.153
T rhythmic music]

18:42.288 --> 18:43.754
Look what the
cat dragged in.

18:43.756 --> 18:44.688
[marcie chuckles]

18:44.757 --> 18:46.090
[phone chimes]

18:48.294 --> 18:50.361
Constable myers.

18:52.098 --> 18:53.564
Inspector.

18:53.566 --> 18:55.099
Inspector?

18:55.234 --> 18:56.867
<i> Is that the reward</i>
<i> that you get</i>

18:56.903 --> 18:58.269
For breaking up with
your girlfriend

18:58.404 --> 19:00.504
And working undercover
for four years?

19:00.639 --> 19:02.106
[carson sighs]

19:03.676 --> 19:05.442
It's good to see you.

19:05.478 --> 19:07.077
It's good to see you too.

19:08.414 --> 19:11.782
So did you get the information
I sent you about the phone?

19:11.818 --> 19:14.251
Well, based on basil allen's
phone records,

19:14.287 --> 19:16.154
He was in halifax when
he sent the text.

19:16.289 --> 19:17.521
I mean, that tracks.

19:17.557 --> 19:20.191
However, when we triangulated
his latest cellphone signal

19:20.193 --> 19:21.525
To the nearest cell tower,

19:21.528 --> 19:23.460
The coordinates came
from newfoundland.

19:25.098 --> 19:26.864
Newfoundland?
-Yeah.

19:26.866 --> 19:29.700
His cell has been pinging
from there since yesterday.

19:31.471 --> 19:33.070
One sec.

19:36.809 --> 19:38.376
[phone ringing]

19:38.511 --> 19:39.510
<i> Hello?</i>
-Iris?

19:39.512 --> 19:40.678
Iris:
<i> Yeah.</i>

19:40.747 --> 19:42.479
I need you to catch the
first flight to newfoundland.

19:42.515 --> 19:44.081
Iris:
<i> Newfoundland, okay.</i>

19:44.150 --> 19:45.149
I'll text you the details.

19:45.151 --> 19:46.317
Iris:
<i> Sure thing.</i>

19:46.452 --> 19:48.219
Marcie:
<i> Okay, thank you.</i>

19:50.323 --> 19:52.289
Carson:
<i> Wait, wait, wait,</i>
<i> wait, wait, wait.</i>

19:52.425 --> 19:53.557
You can't just leave.

19:53.593 --> 19:55.192
Come on.

19:55.828 --> 19:57.327
Stay for one drink.

19:59.165 --> 20:00.698
Okay, one drink.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.404
♪ every day gonna
find a way

20:07.406 --> 20:08.639
<i> ♪ when things go wrong</i>

20:08.708 --> 20:10.307
<i> ♪ it never feels right</i>

20:10.443 --> 20:13.377
<i> ♪ some will say you</i>
<i> can breathe a life</i>

20:13.413 --> 20:16.180
<i> ♪ make it worth it</i>

20:16.315 --> 20:19.216
<i> ♪ have a feeling</i>

20:19.351 --> 20:22.053
<i> ♪ I am worth it</i>

20:22.188 --> 20:25.055
♪ but I won't
accept defeat

20:25.124 --> 20:27.591
♪ I've been
through it all ♪

20:27.594 --> 20:29.059
Hey.

20:29.596 --> 20:31.028
No marcie?

20:32.665 --> 20:34.131
Oh.

20:41.407 --> 20:44.809
Two kids! No way.

20:44.811 --> 20:47.611
Yep, twin girls.

20:47.613 --> 20:49.947
I think I see some grey
hairs coming through.

20:50.082 --> 20:51.882
Oh, you like 'em?

20:51.951 --> 20:55.352
I'm sure your wife thinks
that you're a real zaddy.

20:55.488 --> 20:57.288
I don't know
what that means.

20:57.423 --> 20:59.190
Trust me,
it's a compliment.

20:59.325 --> 21:01.591
And, um, no wife.

21:02.595 --> 21:04.361
Hard to keep a
relationship in this job.

21:04.497 --> 21:05.829
Yeah.

21:06.532 --> 21:07.398
So how's your family?

21:07.533 --> 21:08.899
They're fine.
They're good.

21:11.304 --> 21:14.071
I've been avoiding my dad.

21:14.073 --> 21:15.672
Why?

21:15.674 --> 21:19.710
I remembered something about
my aunt rolanda's death

21:19.845 --> 21:22.780
And I've just been
afraid to tell him.

21:22.849 --> 21:25.216
Marcie diggs I know
isn't afraid of anything.

21:25.218 --> 21:27.017
It's strange, right?

21:27.153 --> 21:28.752
[phone chiming]

21:28.821 --> 21:29.954
[soft dramatic music]

21:30.089 --> 21:32.790
Damn, I gotta go.

21:33.459 --> 21:34.792
Just remember,

21:34.861 --> 21:36.393
Whatever comes your way,

21:36.462 --> 21:38.595
You're gonna crush
it as usual.

21:39.866 --> 21:41.265
Thanks.

21:43.903 --> 21:45.602
[upbeat club music]

21:45.672 --> 21:47.004
Mmm.

21:48.408 --> 21:50.407
Marcie:
<i> Hey, sorry I'm late.</i>

21:50.443 --> 21:51.475
Did I miss anything? Hi.

21:51.610 --> 21:54.611
First set, but they'll be
back up in a few minutes.

21:54.647 --> 21:57.148
Good father, good manager.

21:57.150 --> 21:59.617
Austin:
<i> Howard's only problem is he</i>
<i>spends too long in the bathroom.</i>

21:59.752 --> 22:00.984
Ooh, you're one to talk.

22:01.120 --> 22:02.619
[austin chuckles]

22:04.590 --> 22:06.357
Screening your
old man's calls?

22:06.492 --> 22:07.624
I've been busy.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.126
Mmhmm.

22:10.896 --> 22:12.263
Hi.

22:14.266 --> 22:15.699
Hey yourself.

22:19.238 --> 22:20.837
Where were you?

22:21.374 --> 22:22.573
Case stuff.

22:22.642 --> 22:24.441
And I had to meet
with carson.

22:25.011 --> 22:26.042
Carson myers?

22:26.079 --> 22:27.044
Howard:
<i> Y'all made it!</i>

22:27.113 --> 22:28.712
Marcie:
<i> Yeah, of course.</i>

22:28.781 --> 22:30.447
Emily said these
artists are incredible.

22:30.516 --> 22:32.116
Austin:
<i> They are.</i>

22:32.185 --> 22:34.518
It's good to have the
family back together again.

22:34.520 --> 22:36.020
Just like old times.

22:36.822 --> 22:37.721
<i> I'm glad you and emily</i>

22:37.790 --> 22:39.256
Found your way back
to each other again.

22:39.292 --> 22:41.191
Dad, enough.

22:41.193 --> 22:43.227
So I'm an old man who
believes in second chances.

22:43.296 --> 22:44.661
Okay, austin.

22:44.731 --> 22:47.631
Well, at least there'll be one
decent son-in-law in the family.

22:50.737 --> 22:52.269
Drinks?

22:52.338 --> 22:54.071
I'm gonna grab a soda.

22:54.073 --> 22:55.406
Marcie:
<i> Yeah, that'd be great.</i>

22:55.541 --> 22:57.408
Hey, you okay?

22:58.478 --> 23:00.043
You bet.

23:01.681 --> 23:03.413
How's things in winnipeg?

23:03.449 --> 23:07.684
It feels nice to start
new someplace else.

23:07.720 --> 23:08.619
No baggage.

23:08.754 --> 23:10.154
Hmm.

23:10.823 --> 23:12.356
Glad you're happy.

23:12.358 --> 23:13.824
I am.

23:14.761 --> 23:17.428
Speaking of baggage,
are you and mom?

23:17.563 --> 23:19.430
Is this really happening?

23:19.565 --> 23:20.497
You're right.

23:20.533 --> 23:21.532
I'm the last person
who should judge

23:21.534 --> 23:23.099
Someone else's
relationship choices.

23:23.136 --> 23:24.734
Water under the bridge.

23:25.671 --> 23:26.570
You were right though.

23:26.639 --> 23:28.172
[doug chuckles]

23:32.645 --> 23:34.244
I want to apologize.

23:36.015 --> 23:38.148
I've had a long
time to reflect and

23:40.586 --> 23:42.519
I shouldn't have
said what I said.

23:43.423 --> 23:44.955
It wasn't fair to you.

23:49.295 --> 23:51.328
So you're interested in
working at the clinic?

23:51.364 --> 23:52.929
Oh, absolutely not.

23:54.066 --> 23:55.666
I couldn't turn down a
free ticket to halifax.

23:55.735 --> 23:56.667
Ahh.

23:56.736 --> 23:58.068
Plus, I know you
hate surprises

23:58.070 --> 23:59.402
And I wanted to see
what you were gonna do.

23:59.439 --> 24:00.871
[both laugh]

24:04.811 --> 24:08.278
So it seems like you're actually
gonna go through with this?

24:10.183 --> 24:11.548
I don't know.

24:11.584 --> 24:13.149
I'm feeling...

24:14.187 --> 24:15.652
Manipulated?

24:16.322 --> 24:17.754
That's a word for it.

24:17.790 --> 24:19.890
Keeping you in the dark,
it's weird.

24:20.960 --> 24:22.759
A partnership without trust.

24:28.000 --> 24:29.500
Another g&t, please.

24:30.603 --> 24:32.035
Andrea:
<i> Hey.</i>

24:33.139 --> 24:34.805
Whoa, what's
with the outfit?

24:34.807 --> 24:36.240
What outfit?

24:37.777 --> 24:39.276
And why are you laughing?

24:40.746 --> 24:42.212
That's not weird.

24:42.248 --> 24:44.615
Shouldn't you have
left town by now?

24:44.750 --> 24:46.217
I'll leave town when I'm
good and ready, thank you.

24:46.352 --> 24:48.986
Andrea:
<i> Oh, stubborn.</i>

24:48.988 --> 24:50.787
I like that.

24:50.857 --> 24:53.623
Well, the clawfords
mean business.

24:54.594 --> 24:55.726
So do I.

24:55.795 --> 24:56.794
You don't know me.

24:56.796 --> 24:58.795
Andrea:
<i> I know more than you think.</i>

24:58.831 --> 25:00.430
<i> Vivian jefferson, eh?</i>

25:03.603 --> 25:06.403
Bartender:
<i> I didn't realize you</i>
<i> and andrea were friends.</i>

25:07.807 --> 25:09.940
<i> Any friend of</i>
<i> the clawfords.</i>

25:10.075 --> 25:11.609
It's on the house.

25:11.611 --> 25:13.611
Heeey!

25:13.613 --> 25:15.178
Andrea clawford?

25:20.853 --> 25:26.857
[tense dramatic music]

25:26.859 --> 25:30.160
♪

25:30.196 --> 25:33.964
[upbeat club music]

25:34.099 --> 25:35.565
♪ yeah, I finished cryin' ♪

25:35.601 --> 25:40.971
[muffled singing]

25:41.574 --> 25:42.873
So how's your day?

25:42.942 --> 25:44.407
Great.

25:45.878 --> 25:48.845
You, uh, you get my
condolences about cliff?

25:48.881 --> 25:50.614
I know you two got on.

25:50.650 --> 25:52.215
Oh, that's rich.

25:53.686 --> 25:55.119
Excuse me?

25:55.254 --> 25:57.854
I said "that's rich."

25:58.925 --> 26:01.258
As in it's rich you
should be offering me

26:01.393 --> 26:02.959
Condolences on a death.

26:03.930 --> 26:05.663
I don't exactly
know what you mean.

26:05.798 --> 26:07.364
Of course you don't.

26:09.335 --> 26:11.068
Look, I know things between
us haven't been great,

26:11.070 --> 26:14.071
But I'd really like to know
what exactly is your problem?

26:14.073 --> 26:15.672
Death seems to just
follow you around,

26:15.708 --> 26:16.873
Doesn't it?

26:16.909 --> 26:18.475
Like the damn grim reaper.

26:21.213 --> 26:23.213
You know what?

26:23.215 --> 26:25.215
I'm tired of taking
your garbage.

26:25.251 --> 26:28.051
<i> It's not my fault that</i>
<i> rolanda died, okay?!</i>

26:29.422 --> 26:30.421
[avery groans]

26:30.423 --> 26:31.355
Marcie:
<i> No!</i>

26:31.424 --> 26:32.990
[glasses breaking]
[women gasping]

26:34.760 --> 26:35.826
Velma:
<i> Stop!</i>

26:35.961 --> 26:37.828
Yo, yo, yo.

26:37.963 --> 26:39.063
It's all right,
it's all right.

26:39.065 --> 26:40.196
It's all right.

26:40.232 --> 26:41.565
Let it go.

26:41.567 --> 26:43.133
Velma:
<i> What on earth?</i>

26:44.904 --> 26:47.303
What the hell has
gotten into you?

26:49.041 --> 26:50.040
Me?

26:50.076 --> 26:51.908
Why don't you talk
to your father?

26:51.944 --> 26:53.743
I'm tired of apologizing,
marcie.

26:56.716 --> 26:58.215
I'll see you at home.

27:02.788 --> 27:08.659
[soft peaceful music]

27:08.728 --> 27:18.669
♪

27:18.804 --> 27:26.009
♪

27:26.012 --> 27:27.544
Walt:
<i> Nice wood, sis.</i>

27:28.614 --> 27:29.880
Sis?

27:30.015 --> 27:30.947
My bad.

27:30.983 --> 27:32.749
I didn't mean any offence.

27:32.785 --> 27:34.885
But this here rhino-chaser

27:34.887 --> 27:36.620
Won't do you much good
in the atlantic.

27:37.490 --> 27:39.189
Maybe in santa cruz.

27:42.495 --> 27:44.161
Do you work here?

27:44.230 --> 27:45.829
Do I work here?

27:46.532 --> 27:48.298
Yes, I'm at your service.

27:49.135 --> 27:50.534
Marcie:
<i> Oh.</i>

27:52.338 --> 27:53.903
You seem kinda high.

27:54.039 --> 27:55.973
Shh, don't tell my employer.

27:56.108 --> 27:58.442
So then we've established
that you don't work here.

27:58.444 --> 28:00.243
<i> And if you're trying</i>
<i> to flirt with me,</i>

28:00.378 --> 28:02.246
I'm really not
interested so.

28:02.381 --> 28:04.181
Wait, wait, before you go.

28:04.183 --> 28:06.983
Look, this log here,
it's an original.

28:08.320 --> 28:10.286
It's got your name
written all over it.

28:14.727 --> 28:17.293
Okay, well take care.

28:18.631 --> 28:20.530
I'll see you on the ripples.

28:20.566 --> 28:27.370
[ominous music]

28:31.577 --> 28:32.576
[phone ringing]

28:32.645 --> 28:34.444
Avery:
<i> Avery mueller.</i>

28:34.480 --> 28:35.679
It's me.

28:35.814 --> 28:37.948
Iris, surprised
to hear from you.

28:37.950 --> 28:39.883
I thought you'd be
in newfoundland.

28:39.885 --> 28:41.317
I am.

28:42.855 --> 28:44.420
Everything okay?

28:45.591 --> 28:47.690
I thought I'd take you up
on your offer for an ear.

28:49.562 --> 28:51.095
<i> Bit of a rough morning.</i>

28:52.698 --> 28:54.231
Okay, I'm here.

28:55.201 --> 28:56.633
Iris:
<i> It's just...</i>

28:59.739 --> 29:02.472
Cliff was a
really good guy.

29:02.541 --> 29:04.274
<i> He didn't deserve</i>
<i> to die like that.</i>

29:05.611 --> 29:08.979
It's just not fair,
avery, none of it.

29:09.114 --> 29:10.680
Avery:
<i> You're right, it's not.</i>

29:11.784 --> 29:18.655
But [sighs] it's gonna
get better, okay iris?

29:18.691 --> 29:20.123
Yeah.

29:21.861 --> 29:23.393
Coach:
<i> Hustle man, hustle.</i>

29:26.232 --> 29:27.131
Hey.

29:27.266 --> 29:28.532
Hey.

29:28.534 --> 29:31.802
So basil and the others play
in this soccer league very week.

29:31.804 --> 29:33.337
Coach:
<i> Practise and learn.</i>

29:34.940 --> 29:36.473
Marcie:
<i> Ned's here.</i>

29:37.977 --> 29:38.809
[background chatter]

29:38.878 --> 29:40.611
You should've seen him,
he was so-

29:40.746 --> 29:42.746
Hi, hi, do-do
you remember me?

29:42.881 --> 29:44.214
I'm basil allen's friend.

29:44.349 --> 29:45.482
We've been looking for him.

29:45.484 --> 29:46.516
Have you seen him?

29:46.519 --> 29:47.951
Wait, we're trying
to locate him.

29:47.987 --> 29:50.053
<i> Have you seen him?</i>

29:50.055 --> 29:51.454
Trudy:
<i> Excuse me-</i>

29:53.358 --> 29:55.158
Ned:
<i> What are you</i>
<i> two doing here?</i>

29:55.194 --> 29:56.893
It's a public field,
mr. Flores.

29:56.929 --> 29:59.763
You're trying to ask our workers
questions behind my back.

29:59.898 --> 30:01.198
You don't own them.

30:01.267 --> 30:02.699
We can talk to them
if we want to.

30:02.834 --> 30:06.569
I already told you,
basil allen ran off.

30:06.605 --> 30:08.939
You and I both know
that's not the truth.

30:09.074 --> 30:11.108
What are you talking about?

30:11.243 --> 30:13.243
Basil didn't run off.

30:13.279 --> 30:14.845
He was loaded into
the back of a truck

30:14.847 --> 30:16.246
And taken to newfoundland.

30:16.315 --> 30:19.583
<i> Now, you lied mr. Flores,</i>
<i> and I want to know why.</i>

30:20.919 --> 30:23.587
I don't know where
you got that from

30:23.589 --> 30:25.388
But you need to
get outta here.

30:26.392 --> 30:27.858
Make me.

30:27.927 --> 30:34.130
[tense dramatic music]

30:36.602 --> 30:42.639
Oft dramatic music]

30:42.708 --> 30:45.209
I'm not gonna apologize
if that's why you're here.

30:48.947 --> 30:50.280
Marcie:
<i> But are you okay?</i>

30:50.415 --> 30:51.949
Old man still has
fight in him.

30:52.084 --> 30:54.218
Well, that definitely
wasn't up for debate.

30:55.688 --> 30:58.154
<i> Look, I get the instinct to</i>
<i> blame avery for what happened,</i>

30:58.190 --> 30:59.155
I did too.

30:59.191 --> 31:01.324
I don't blame him.

31:01.360 --> 31:04.428
But he could have
been better to her.

31:04.563 --> 31:06.129
That's hard to forget.

31:08.601 --> 31:11.567
[sighs] there's
something else that I, um,

31:13.038 --> 31:15.572
That I'm here to
talk to you about.

31:15.574 --> 31:17.040
Hmm, yeah.

31:19.044 --> 31:20.843
[marcie sighs]

31:23.048 --> 31:28.418
So I've been having
these, uh, dreams

31:30.188 --> 31:32.855
About the dominican trip
that I took with rolanda.

31:32.892 --> 31:33.790
[austin chuckles]

31:33.926 --> 31:35.325
I remember that trip.

31:35.327 --> 31:38.761
You two were so excited,
couldn't stop talking about it.

31:39.832 --> 31:44.301
You know, at first,
I, uh, I didn't know why

31:44.436 --> 31:46.169
<i> I was having these dreams,</i>

31:46.205 --> 31:48.005
<i> But then my</i>
<i> therapist told me</i>

31:48.007 --> 31:50.741
That it was because
of the shooting.

31:50.876 --> 31:56.313
It-it brought up all of
these buried memories

31:56.382 --> 31:58.115
<i> And I remembered...</i>

32:01.887 --> 32:03.453
That rolanda wasn't...

32:05.023 --> 32:06.589
She wasn't doing well.

32:09.828 --> 32:11.761
She tried to take her
life on that trip.

32:13.232 --> 32:17.033
And I knew and I
didn't tell you.

32:19.672 --> 32:23.440
[sombre music]

32:23.442 --> 32:27.243
There were other times,
other attempts.

32:29.281 --> 32:31.114
When ro was younger,

32:31.183 --> 32:32.782
I knew there was an issue.

32:35.120 --> 32:36.853
We tried to get
her help but the-

32:37.589 --> 32:39.056
Folks weren't having it.

32:40.392 --> 32:42.459
Didn't want people in
the community talking.

32:43.929 --> 32:47.697
I still feel guilt
wondering if I could have

32:50.402 --> 32:51.935
Done more.

32:56.475 --> 32:58.341
I should have told you.

32:59.511 --> 33:02.179
I just loved her so much, dad.

33:02.181 --> 33:08.084
[sombre gentle music]

33:08.220 --> 33:10.620
Well, melanie won't
make the wedding.

33:10.622 --> 33:12.088
She's stuck in australia.

33:12.124 --> 33:14.057
Ah, that's too bad.

33:15.294 --> 33:16.759
It is!

33:16.795 --> 33:19.029
And I never thought I'd
say that about my sister

33:19.164 --> 33:20.296
After everything.

33:20.298 --> 33:21.264
Old drama's still drama

33:21.400 --> 33:24.835
And this wedding has to
go off without a hitch.

33:24.837 --> 33:26.436
Speaking of that,

33:27.673 --> 33:29.239
<i> Which of these invitation</i>
<i> samples do you prefer?</i>

33:30.342 --> 33:31.241
Aren't they the same?

33:31.376 --> 33:32.509
Unhelpful!

33:32.578 --> 33:35.144
I need to make
up my mind here.

33:35.180 --> 33:36.646
Relatable.

33:37.182 --> 33:38.214
Eskasoni?

33:38.216 --> 33:40.417
Full steam ahead,
office is packed.

33:40.552 --> 33:41.851
Although I'm starting
to regret it.

33:41.987 --> 33:43.252
Because of viv's leah stunt?

33:43.288 --> 33:45.422
She pitched
leadership to me,

33:45.557 --> 33:47.490
Taking the reigns, autonomy.

33:49.128 --> 33:51.061
But it felt like she
was working me.

33:52.131 --> 33:53.530
I didn't like it.

33:53.532 --> 33:56.199
So you're afraid that
marcie might be right?

33:56.235 --> 33:58.468
That vivian's just
chasing you to hurt her?

33:58.603 --> 34:00.670
<i> Don't worry about</i>
<i> vivian's motives.</i>

34:00.706 --> 34:02.205
What do you want?

34:02.207 --> 34:05.675
I don't want to choose between
my community and marcie.

34:05.677 --> 34:08.011
Even when you
couldn't come home,

34:08.146 --> 34:10.080
Your community's
always been with you.

34:10.215 --> 34:11.747
<i> Marcie's your friend,</i>

34:11.784 --> 34:13.517
<i> More than that, a sister.</i>

34:14.920 --> 34:17.287
You'll always have
your community

34:17.289 --> 34:19.489
And marcie will always
see you as a brother.

34:20.793 --> 34:23.293
<i> This is about you deciding</i>
<i> what feels right for you.</i>

34:25.630 --> 34:27.063
Thanks, mich.

34:27.966 --> 34:30.100
[gentle music]

34:30.235 --> 34:31.734
Ah, this one.

34:33.072 --> 34:34.204
Vellum?!

34:34.273 --> 34:37.207
No, we gotta go with linen.

34:37.276 --> 34:39.242
[michelle giggles]

34:40.312 --> 34:41.777
Brian:
<i> Ms. Diggs.</i>

34:42.848 --> 34:48.518
<i> Trespassing, harassment,</i>
<i> need I go on?</i>

34:48.520 --> 34:53.556
<i> You have been quite the</i>
<i> thorn in my employees side.</i>

34:53.625 --> 34:54.691
Mr. Clawford.

34:54.826 --> 34:56.726
Brian, please.

34:56.861 --> 34:58.661
Basil allen has been
missing for days

34:58.730 --> 35:00.330
And instead of
giving us answers,

35:00.465 --> 35:02.933
Your entire operation
has closed ranks.

35:03.068 --> 35:06.335
I assure you that this is
nothing but a misunderstanding.

35:06.371 --> 35:08.037
Marcie:
<i> Well then I'll ask</i>
<i> you once more.</i>

35:08.107 --> 35:10.373
Where is basil allen?

35:10.409 --> 35:13.143
I'll look up his file so we
can clear up this matter.

35:17.850 --> 35:19.916
Oh right, here it is.

35:19.918 --> 35:21.918
[keyboard clacking]

35:22.888 --> 35:24.020
Hmm.

35:24.089 --> 35:27.991
[ominous music]

35:28.126 --> 35:29.959
[keyboard clacking]

35:29.995 --> 35:31.328
Brian:
<i> Right.</i>

35:31.463 --> 35:33.629
There seems to have
been a clerical error

35:33.665 --> 35:34.830
And mr. Allen
was transferred

35:34.867 --> 35:37.166
To our newfoundland
farm by mistake.

35:37.168 --> 35:39.035
You know you're not supposed
to move migrant workers

35:39.037 --> 35:40.836
From their initial
location of employment.

35:40.973 --> 35:44.374
I'm well aware of the rules
of the program, ms. Diggs.

35:44.443 --> 35:45.976
As I said,
it was an error.

35:45.978 --> 35:47.777
Easily fixed.

35:47.846 --> 35:50.246
I'll have him back in
nova scotia by this evening.

35:50.849 --> 35:51.781
Ned:
<i> Brian.</i>

35:51.783 --> 35:53.382
Ned.

35:55.154 --> 35:56.653
Thanks for stepping
in again last night.

35:56.655 --> 35:59.355
<i> That's been bubbling</i>
<i> up for some time.</i>

35:59.357 --> 36:01.391
Still can't believe you
punched avery in the face.

36:01.526 --> 36:03.393
<i> How come you never</i>
<i> punched this one</i>

36:03.528 --> 36:05.028
When we were
going through it?

36:05.097 --> 36:08.131
Anger is like a poison.

36:09.401 --> 36:12.068
My therapist says you gotta
let it out when it comes.

36:12.137 --> 36:15.338
<i> If you bottle it up</i>
<i> sooner or later you burst.</i>

36:15.340 --> 36:17.540
And burst I did.

36:17.543 --> 36:18.875
You go to therapy?

36:18.877 --> 36:21.277
I did a while back,

36:21.313 --> 36:22.545
You know, self-care

36:22.614 --> 36:25.215
Or whatever the millennials
are talking about these days.

36:25.350 --> 36:26.882
Well it did you good.

36:27.953 --> 36:29.518
I gotta hit the washroom.

36:30.956 --> 36:32.521
Bartender:
<i> Here you go, gentlemen.</i>

36:33.558 --> 36:35.091
Austin:
<i> I'll get this.</i>

36:36.195 --> 36:37.793
You sure, mr. Diggs?

36:38.764 --> 36:41.097
You got in the way
of a fist from me.

36:41.166 --> 36:42.966
Least I can do is get lunch.

36:42.968 --> 36:44.333
Thanks.

36:45.303 --> 36:46.369
Hey, can you give me a sec?

36:46.504 --> 36:48.038
I just want to check in with
ava about tonight's show.

36:48.173 --> 36:49.906
Of course, do your thing.

36:55.514 --> 36:56.913
Howard:
<i> Hi.</i>

36:57.482 --> 36:59.049
Alright?

36:59.184 --> 37:00.917
<i> You're gonna do</i>
<i> that duet from,</i>

37:00.986 --> 37:02.719
<i> The one that we</i>
<i> talked about, right?</i>

37:02.721 --> 37:04.520
<i> Yeah. Okay 'cause</i>
<i> that's my favourite.</i>

37:05.824 --> 37:07.724
<i> I mean, you know</i>
<i> that's my favourite.</i>

37:07.726 --> 37:09.726
[austin sighs]

37:09.861 --> 37:12.328
[tense dramatic music]

37:12.364 --> 37:14.597
Howard:
<i> So how is my</i>
<i> favourite chanteuse?</i>

37:14.666 --> 37:15.731
Ava:
<i> Right as rain, baby.</i>

37:15.767 --> 37:17.867
Howard:
<i> Yeah? [laughs]</i>

37:17.936 --> 37:19.669
<i> So I'm just thinking...</i>

37:22.340 --> 37:23.807
Everything okay?

37:24.676 --> 37:25.875
Don't disrespect my daughter.

37:29.715 --> 37:31.214
That-that isn't...

37:31.216 --> 37:32.348
That's not anything.

37:32.484 --> 37:34.317
Oh I know exactly
what it is

37:34.452 --> 37:36.152
Because I've been in
your position and-

37:36.221 --> 37:37.754
Y'all ready?

37:39.091 --> 37:40.690
Sure thing.

37:42.094 --> 37:43.560
Thanks again, mr. Diggs.

37:47.032 --> 37:53.036
[ominous music]

37:53.038 --> 38:07.317
♪

38:07.452 --> 38:09.986
Hey, do you guys have
a lost and found?

38:10.055 --> 38:11.321
I was on a boat
about a week ago

38:11.323 --> 38:13.390
<i> And I seem to have</i>
<i> lost my phone.</i>

38:13.392 --> 38:14.991
We do.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.659
Right over here.

38:18.397 --> 38:24.134
[ominous music]

38:24.269 --> 38:25.268
Gloves?

38:25.270 --> 38:27.404
Who knows what
horrors are in here.

38:27.406 --> 38:29.072
Fair enough.

38:29.207 --> 38:35.411
[suspenseful music]

38:35.547 --> 38:41.417
[suspenseful music swells]

38:45.824 --> 38:46.823
Avery:
<i> How'd it go?</i>

38:46.825 --> 38:49.191
Marcie:
<i> It was good. Needed.</i>

38:49.227 --> 38:50.626
Avery:
<i> Well did he apologize?</i>

38:50.662 --> 38:52.462
It wasn't the
"thrilla on agricola".

38:52.464 --> 38:54.029
<i> I mean, it was...</i>

38:54.833 --> 38:57.166
It was about rolanda.

38:57.869 --> 38:59.502
Oh? Okay.

39:01.373 --> 39:04.307
There are things about
my aunt that were

39:06.244 --> 39:08.477
Unclear until now.

39:10.115 --> 39:11.648
About her mental health.

39:12.851 --> 39:14.918
<i> She was struggling</i>
<i> with depression</i>

39:15.053 --> 39:19.923
<i> And, um, there had been</i>
<i> other suicide attempts.</i>

39:21.226 --> 39:22.325
<i> Just before I brought</i>
<i> her into m&m,</i>

39:22.394 --> 39:23.326
<i> Just before she met you,</i>

39:23.461 --> 39:24.861
<i> She, um...</i>

39:24.996 --> 39:27.597
She actually tried
to kill herself.

39:27.599 --> 39:30.300
<i> And I didn't tell anyone.</i>

39:30.435 --> 39:31.968
I just thought...

39:33.105 --> 39:35.872
<i> I thought it'd been</i>
<i> the only time but...</i>

39:35.941 --> 39:37.674
[marcie sighs]

39:37.676 --> 39:39.476
Marcie:
<i> Just knowing all of this...</i>

39:42.748 --> 39:44.280
It's freeing.

39:45.584 --> 39:48.485
Marcie, I always had a different
impression of her death.

39:50.355 --> 39:51.888
The way it played out.

39:51.957 --> 39:55.692
And that's partially me.

39:58.830 --> 40:00.330
I was angry.

40:02.033 --> 40:03.599
I needed someone to blame.

40:04.869 --> 40:07.770
<i> But none of us are</i>
<i> responsible for her death.</i>

40:10.642 --> 40:12.107
Yeah.

40:12.944 --> 40:14.577
Yeah, well I'm
happy for you.

40:16.047 --> 40:17.847
I'm happy you
figured this out.

40:20.252 --> 40:21.718
Yeah.

40:21.720 --> 40:27.724
[soft dramatic music]

40:27.726 --> 40:31.261
♪

40:31.263 --> 40:32.862
[knocking on door]

40:33.865 --> 40:35.265
Deja vu.

40:36.267 --> 40:37.934
I figured you'd
be in eskasoni.

40:40.972 --> 40:42.771
Forgot to give
you something.

40:46.578 --> 40:48.144
Open it.

40:55.353 --> 40:57.152
<i> Now the cardstock's linen,</i>

40:57.189 --> 40:59.088
<i> Which I've been</i>
<i> told is important.</i>

41:01.793 --> 41:04.694
I wasn't as supportive
as I could have been.

41:06.297 --> 41:09.966
I just, I-I wanted you to feel
like this was your firm, too.

41:10.035 --> 41:11.634
I do.

41:12.771 --> 41:13.836
That's why I want to do
the legal clinic here

41:13.839 --> 41:15.704
At mda with you.

41:17.809 --> 41:18.641
Are you sure?

41:18.710 --> 41:20.210
Doug:
<i> Yeah, I'm sure.</i>

41:21.346 --> 41:22.712
Anyway, I got a stack
of files on my desk

41:22.781 --> 41:24.580
The size of a
large toddler so.

41:26.318 --> 41:27.884
Marcie:
<i> Doug?</i>

41:30.322 --> 41:31.721
Thank you.

